JOHANNESBURG – A Johannesburg metro bus has caught fire on Kingsway next to the University of Johannesburg on Tuesday evening. Videos of the bus engulfed in huge flames circulated on social media. Metro bus spokesperson Nkosinathi Nkabinde confirmed a Metro bus was on fire. He said the cause of the fire is not yet known and that no one was injured. READ: Bus catches fire on R24/N12 highway “At the moment I cannot give you more details because our team is going to the scene to investigate,” Nkabinde said. “It is one of the new Euro five buses… I cannot confirm the cause of the fire -- whether it was an engine problem or cable problem.” “At this moment the cause is not established but there are no signs of attack,” he said. eNCA